Your origin points to the main LLVM repo, which you can't push to. You need to push to your fork instead. Check your remotes:

bash
git remote -v

If your fork isn't listed, add it:

bash
git remote add fork https://github.com/LouisLu060211/llvm-project.git
git push fork fix-affine-for-fold-detached-block

If a remote for your fork already exists under some name, just push to that name instead of fork.

The commit itself already succeeded, so nothing is lost. Once the push goes through, the PR updates automatically since it tracks the branch on your fork.

Two follow-ups:

Optional cleanup so this doesn't bite you again: make origin your fork and keep the main repo as upstream:
bash
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/LouisLu060211/llvm-project.git
git remote add upstream https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project.git
git push origin fix-affine-for-fold-detached-block
I didn't see you run the test before committing. Before you consider this done, run:
bash
<path-to-build>/bin/llvm-lit -v mlir/test/Conversion/FuncToLLVM/func-to-llvm.mlir

If it fails, fix it and amend the commit with git commit --amend --no-edit, then push again with -f if you already pushed. Reviewers will run this in CI, so better to catch it now.
